---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navigation from '../../components/Navigation.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="My Sony WF-1000XM3 & WF-1000XM4 Custom EQ Settings - Buyun Wang">
  <Navigation />
  <main class="pt-32 pb-24 px-8 min-h-screen">
    <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <header class="mb-12">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">
          <span class="px-2 py-1 bg-gray-100 rounded-md text-xs font-medium">Audio</span>
          <span>Mar 20, 2022</span>
          <span>•</span>
          <span>5 min read</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-6">My Sony WF-1000XM3 & WF-1000XM4 Custom EQ Settings</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-4">Optimized equalizer settings for Sony's flagship earbuds from an ex-Sony employee.</p>
        <div class="border-t pt-4">
          <a href="https://medium.com/@buyunwang/my-sony-wf-1000xm3-wf-1000xm4-custom-eq-settings-b2244f5ef9d0" 
             target="_blank" 
             rel="noopener noreferrer"
             class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 text-sm font-medium">
            Read original on Medium →
          </a>
        </div>
      </header>
      
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">
          Being a long time Sony fan and an ex employee, I am very fortunate to have both the wf-1000xm3 & wf-1000xm4 in my possession. And I just want to share my favourite EQ settings for EDM/Hiphop based on the differences of their tonality and tuning.
        </p>

        <div class="my-10">
          <img src="/images/sony-earbuds-1.jpg" alt="wf1000xm3 vs wf1000xm4" class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-md" />
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-3 text-center">wf1000xm3 vs wf1000xm4</p>
        </div>

        <div class="my-10">
          <img src="/images/sony-earbuds-2.jpg" alt="wf1000xm3 vs wf1000xm4" class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-md" />
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-3 text-center">wf1000xm3 vs wf1000xm4</p>
        </div>

        <p class="mb-10 leading-relaxed">
          I'm quite used to bassy headphones and earbuds before and that is reflected in my tuning below.
        </p>

        <h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-3xl font-bold">WF-1000XM3 Settings</h2>
        
        <div class="my-8">
          <img src="/images/sony-wf1000xm3-eq-settings.jpg" alt="wf1000xm3 Settings" class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-md" />
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-3 text-center">wf1000xm3</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-gray-100 p-6 rounded-lg my-6 border-l-4 border-blue-500">
          <p class="font-mono text-lg">
            400: +2, 1k: +1, 2.5k: +5, 6.3k: +2, 15.6k: +2, ClearBass: +5
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-3xl font-bold">WF-1000XM4 Settings</h2>
        
        <div class="my-8">
          <img src="/images/sony-wf1000xm4-eq-settings.jpg" alt="wf1000xm4 Settings" class="w-full rounded-lg shadow-md" />
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-3 text-center">wf1000xm4</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-gray-100 p-6 rounded-lg my-6 border-l-4 border-green-500">
          <p class="font-mono text-lg">
            400: +2, 1k: +1, 2.5k: +5, 6.3k: +3, 15.6k: +4, ClearBass: +5
          </p>
        </div>

        <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          The out of the box sound from the xm4 is a little darker than the xm3 so I'm giving some extra boost in the treble department but overall these are quite similar. The vocals can be a little bit overshadowed on both of the buds so I'm bringing it up. I love the energy this EQ settings has and the bass is thumping without being too boomy. For other genres of music I'd go with less bass for sure though.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-6 leading-relaxed">
          I was fiddling around with the sliders while listening to Tom Enzy and LissA's "Teach Me How to Love" and holy obi wan kenobi, the sub bass is bouncy with this one.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">
          I'd say Sony nailed it again in terms of ANC, sound quality(sound stage, clarity, instrument separation are all top notch) and battery life with these earbuds. Have fun listening!
        </p>

        <div class="mt-12 p-6 bg-blue-50 rounded-lg border border-blue-200">
          <p class="mb-4 font-semibold text-blue-800">
            <strong>PS:</strong> Amazon is doing discounts on both earphones treat yourself some ANC magic with these affiliate links:
          </p>
          
          <ul class="space-y-2 pl-4">
            <li><a href="https://amzn.to/4arLTL0" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 font-medium">WF-1000XM4</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://amzn.to/4bGpdYq" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800 font-medium">WF-1000XM5</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
